Neglecting air resistance - what does the assumption really mean?", "fibs": ["Answer"]}
{"text": "While treating the topic of projectile motion, we have stated that we assume that the air resistance has no effect on the motion of the projectile.", "fibs": ["topic"]}
{"text": "You must understand what the statement really means.", "fibs": ["statement"]}
{"text": "Friction, force due to viscosity, air resistance are all dissipative forces.", "fibs": ["Friction"]}
{"text": "In the presence of any of such forces opposing motion, any object will lose some part of its initial energy and consequently, momentum too.", "fibs": ["presence"]}
{"text": "Thus, a projectile that traverses a parabolic path would certainly show deviation from its idealised trajectory in the presence of air resistance.", "fibs": ["projectile"]}
{"text": "It will not hit the ground with the same speed with which it was projected from it.", "fibs": ["ground"]}
{"text": "In the absence of air resistance, the x-component of the velocity remains constant and it is only the y-component that undergoes a continuous change.", "fibs": ["absence"]}
{"text": "However, in the presence of air resistance, both of these would get affected.", "fibs": ["presence"]}
{"text": "That would mean that the range would be less than the one given by Eq.", "fibs": ["range"]}
{"text": "Maximum height attained would also be less than that predicted by Eq.", "fibs": ["height"]}
{"text": "Can you then, anticipate the change in the time of flight?", "fibs": ["change"]}
{"text": "In order to avoid air resistance, we will have to perform the experiment in vacuum or under low pressure, which is not easy.", "fibs": ["order"]}
{"text": "When we use a phrase like ‘neglect air resistance’, we imply that the change in parameters such as range, height etc.", "fibs": ["use"]}
{"text": "is much smaller than their values without air resistance.", "fibs": ["air"]}
{"text": "The calculation without air resistance is much simpler than that with air resistance.", "fibs": ["calculation"]}
{"text": "4.11  Uniform circular motion
When an object follows a circular path at a constant speed, the motion of the object is called uniform circular motion.", "fibs": ["motion"]}
{"text": "The word “uniform” refers to the speed, which is uniform (constant) throughout the motion.", "fibs": ["word"]}
{"text": "Suppose an object is moving with uniform speed v in a circle of radius R as shown in Fig.", "fibs": ["object"]}
{"text": "Since the velocity of the object is changing continuously in direction, the object undergoes acceleration.", "fibs": ["velocity"]}
